attachments.fallback: #9237 Downgrading Node version from 20.11.0 to 22.5.1 for DigitalOcean
attachments.text:
*Proposed Changes*

The DigitalOcean buildpack supports the following Node.js runtime versions for Ubuntu 22.04:  
• 4.x - 19.x  
• 20.0.0 - 20.9.0  
• 21.0.0 - 21.7.3  
• 22.0.0 - 22.5.1

Node.js v20.11.0 builds fail during deployment. Downgrading to v22.5.1 resolves the issue.

<https://github.com/orgs/ohcnetwork/teams/care-fe-code-reviewers|@ohcnetwork/care-fe-code-reviewers>

*Merge Checklist*

• Add specs that demonstrate bug / test a new feature.
• Update <https://docs.ohc.network|product documentation>.
• Ensure that UI text is kept in I18n files.
• Prep screenshot or demo video for changelog entry, and attach it to issue.
• Request for Peer Reviews
• Completion of QA

*Summary by CodeRabbit*

• *New Features*  
   • Expanded compatibility by lowering the minimum required Node.js version, allowing users with older versions (>=22.5.1) to run the project successfully.

attachments.fallback: #10535 Added Scripts to Generate headers for CF Pages
attachments.text:
The *HEADERS_64* environment variable defines the header policy, which generates a _headers file to enforce security headers during deployment. This variable can be customized in the deployment environment to implement header policies specific to the requirements.

*Summary by CodeRabbit*

• *New Features*  
   • Added a new environment variable `HEADERS` for specifying various security headers.  
   • Enhanced the installation process to include automated generation of headers, streamlining deployment without altering existing settings.
• *Chores*  
   • Updated the postinstall script to include the execution of a new headers generation script.  
   • Added a new script to read the `HEADERS` variable and write its contents to a file.  
   • Updated `.gitignore` to exclude the generated `_headers` file from version control.
